The general inclusion criteria for relevant research studies were the following: (i) articles had to be published in a peer-review scientific journal;
(ii) studies reporting sensitivity and specificity measures in relation to a histopathological or clinical diagnosis of neurodegenerative diseases;
(iii) studies including large cohorts of subjects (see Table 1 : early diagnosis FDG: range 20-395; Table 2 : differential diagnosis FDG: range 45-297; Table 3 : early diagnosis amyloid: range 13-107);
(iv) studies investigating the prediction of mild cognitive impairment (MCI) to Alzheimer's disease (AD) conversion that retrospectively analyzed the initial characteristics of those who were progressive and those who remained stable.
